        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3 id="what-is-FreeRTOS"><a href="#what-is-FreeRTOS" class="headerlink" title="what is FreeRTOS ?"></a>what is FreeRTOS ?</h3><p><a href="https://www.freertos.org/">freertos</a>    </p><blockquote><p>Real-time operating system for microcontrollers and small microprocessors</p></blockquote><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">FreeRTOS is a market-leading embedded system RTOS supporting 40+ processor architectures </span><br><span class="line">with a small memory footprint, fast execution times, and cutting-edge RTOS features and </span><br><span class="line">libraries including Symmetric Multiprocessing (SMP), a thread-safe TCP stack with IPv6 </span><br><span class="line">support, and seamless integration with cloud services. </span><br><span class="line">It’s open-source and actively supported and maintained.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>]]></content>
      
      
